===Etymology 1===
From {{etyl|enm}}, from {{etyl|ang}} {{term|pund||a pound, weight|lang=ang}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{recons|pundan||pound, weight|lang=gem-pro}}, an early borrowing from {{etyl|la}} {{term|pondo|pondō|lang=la|by weight}}, ablative form of {{term|pondus|lang=la||weight}}, from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{recons|pend-|lang=ine-pro}}, {{recons|spend-||to pull, stretch|lang=ine-pro}}. Cognate with Dutch {{term|pond|lang=nl}}, German {{term|Pfund|lang=de}}, Swedish {{term|pund|lang=sv}}.

